          <lg n="1">
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-972-CWJS-line-1" n="1">In Reading Your Letter alone in my Hackney</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-972-CWJS-line-2" n="2">Your damnable Riddle my Poor Brains did rack nigh</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-972-CWJS-line-3" n="3">And when with much labour the Matter I crackt</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-972-CWJS-line-4" n="4">I found You mistaken in matter of Fact</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-972-CWJS-line-5" n="5"><lb/>A Woman's no Sieve (for with that You begin)</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-972-CWJS-line-6" n="6">Because She letts out more than she takes in;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-972-CWJS-line-7" n="7">And that she's a Riddle can never be right</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-972-CWJS-line-8" n="8">For a Riddle is dark and a Woman is Light.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-972-CWJS-line-9" n="9">But grant her a Sieve, I can say something Archer</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-972-CWJS-line-10" n="10">Pray What is a Man? He's a fine Linnen searcher.</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-972-CWJS-line-11" n="11"><lb/>Now tell me a Thing that wants Interpretation</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-972-CWJS-line-12" n="12">What Name for a Maid was the first Man's Damnation?</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-972-CWJS-line-13" n="13">If Your Worship will please to Explain me this Rebus</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-972-CWJS-line-14" n="14">I swear from henceforward You shall be my Ph≈ìbus<lb/><space>J<hi rend="superscript">n</hi>/hi&gt;: Swift</space></l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-972-CWJS-line-15" n="15">From My Hackney Coach<lb/>Sep<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>: 11<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>: 1718 past 12 at Noon.</l>
          </lg>
        </div>
